fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.transformation.atl.helper

Class AbstractATLTransformationHelper<ES,ET>

  • Object
    • AbstractATLTransformationHelper<ES,ET>
  • Type Parameters:
    ES - the type representing source elements
    ET - the type representing target elements
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    InPlaceATLTransformationHelper

    public abstract class AbstractATLTransformationHelper<ES,ET>
extends Object
    Defines the ATL primitives that should be implemented to support ATL execution in generated Gremlin code.

    This helper is used in the Gremlin code generated from the ATL transformation plugin. Provided methods are called within the generated code to avoid complex (and inefficient) Gremlin instructions.

    This helper is independent of the implicit schema used to represent the model, and delegates all the database accesses to its embedded ModelDatastores.

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:
    ModelDatastore

      • linkReference

        public void linkReference(ET from,
                          Object to,
                          String label,
                          String oppositeLabel,
                          boolean isContainment)
        Links from and to by creating a mapped reference.

        Note that to can be an element of the source model that has to be resolved (declarative binding), or an element of the target model that has been created by the rule (multi-binding rule). If to is in the source model and cannot be resolved (because the corresponding target element has not been created yet) a proxy link (see createProxyLink(Object, Object, String, String, boolean)) is created that will be resolved later (see resolveProxies(Object, Object)).

        The default implementation of this method checks if to is in the source or target model. If it is part of the source model it checks whether the element can be resolved and creates a concrete/proxy link accordingly. If the element is part of the target model a concrete link is created.

        Parameters:
        from - the tail (in the target model) of the link to create
        to - the head of the link to create (from the source or the target model)
        label - the label of the link to create
        oppositeLabel - the label of the opposite reference if it exists
        isContainment - true if the reference is a containment, false otherwise
        See Also:
        linkReference(Object, Iterable, String, String, boolean)

      • linkReference

        public void linkReference(ET from,
                          Iterable<Object> to,
                          String label,
                          String oppositeLabel,
                          boolean isContainment)
        Links from to all the elements in to by creating mapped references.

        Note that to can contain elements of the source model that have to be resolved (declarative binding), or elements of the target model that have been created by the rule (multi-binding rule). If an element in to is in the source model and cannot be resolved (because the corresponding target element has not been created yet) a proxy link (see createProxyLink(Object, Object, String, String, boolean)) is created that will be resolved later (see resolveProxies(Object, Object)).

        The default implementation of this method simply delegates to linkReference(Object, Object, String, String, boolean) by iterating in the provided to Iterable.

        Parameters:
        from - the tail (in the target model) of the links to create
        to - the heads of the links to create (from the source and/or the target model)
        label - the label of the links to create
        oppositeLabel - the label of the opposite reference if it exists
        isContainment - true if the reference is a containment, false otherwise
        See Also:
        linkReference(Object, Object, String, String, boolean)

      • createConcreteLink

        protected void createConcreteLink(ET from,
                                  ET to,
                                  String label,
                                  String oppositeLabel,
                                  boolean isContainment)
        Creates a concrete link between from and to.

        This method is similar to linkReference(Object, Object, String, String, boolean) with a to element in the target model. It creates a concrete mapped reference in the target model between the two elements from and to by using the internal target ModelDatastore.

        The default implementation of this method delegates the reference creation to the underlying target ModelDatastore. It can be extended to add transformation specific behavior.

        Parameters:
        from - the tail (in the target model) of the link to create
        to - the head (in the target model) of the link to create
        label - the label of the link to create
        oppositeLabel - the label of the opposite reference if it exists
        isContainment - true if the reference is a containment, false otherwise
        See Also:
        linkReference(Object, Object, String, String, boolean), linkReference(Object, Iterable, String, String, boolean)

      • createProxyLink

        protected abstract void createProxyLink(ET from,
                                        ES to,
                                        String label,
                                        String oppositeLabel,
                                        boolean isContainment)
        Creates a proxy link between from and to.

        This method is similar to linkReference(Object, Object, String, String, boolean) with a to element in the source model. It creates an cross-model proxy link which is not defined in the source or target ModelDatastore that link the target element from to the source one to.

        Parameters:
        from - the tail (in the target model) of the proxy link to create
        to - the head (in the source model) of the link to create
        label - the label of the proxy link to create
        oppositeLabel - the label of the opposite reference if it exists
        isContainment - true if the reference is a containment, false otherwise
        See Also:
        linkReference(Object, Object, String, String, boolean), linkReference(Object, Iterable, String, String, boolean)

      • resolveProxies

        public abstract void resolveProxies(ES sourceProxy,
                                    ET targetElement)
        Resolves the proxy links connected to sourceProxy by setting their tail to targetElement.

        sourceProxy is an element of the source model that has been transformed and is connected by proxy links to targetElement. Resolving a proxy removes the cross-model proxy links and replaces them by the corresponding link in the target model.

        Parameters:
        sourceProxy - the element that is connected to proxy links
        targetElement - the element that resolves the proxies

      • isResolvable

        public abstract boolean isResolvable(ES sourceProxy)
        Checks if the provided sourceProxy can be resolved.

        sourceProxy is an element of the source model, that may be resolved if it is associated to an element in the target model.

        Parameters:
        sourceProxy - the source element to check
        Returns:
        true if sourceProxy can be resolved, false otherwise

      • resolve

        public abstract ET resolve(ES sourceProxy)
        Resolves the sourceProxy element by retrieving the corresponding target element.

        This method returns an element of the target model that corresponds to the provided sourceProxy. Note that sourceProxy may not be resolvable if the corresponding target element hasn't been created yet (see isResolvable(Object)).

        Parameters:
        sourceProxy - the source element to resolve
        Returns:
        the target element corresponding to sourceProxy if it exists
